In the Fermat Quartic, the curves are restricted by the fact that 
$a, b, c$ are $4$-th powers. This forces the elliptic curves to 
have 4-torsion or 8-torsion points.

# Assuming E is your EllipticCurve and P is a point on it
print(P.order())

To see if your curve is "allowed" to have 4-torsion or 8-torsion 
points globally, you can inspect the entire torsion subgroup
T = E.torsion_subgroup()
print(T)
This will return something like Torsion Subgroup isomorphic to 
Z/4 + Z/1 or Z/8 + Z/1. This tells you the "degree" of the symmetry 
available to that specific $u$ value.


