Isogeny Graphs: Construct the isogeny graph (e.g., 2-isogeny chains or cycles) 
to see if \( E \) belongs to a family.

The isogeny class of \( E \) is related to its modular form. 
Since \( E \) has a degree-2 isogeny:
Its modular form \( fE \) is not CM (complex multiplication) 
but may have a quadratic twist symmetry.
The \( L \)-function of \( E \) and \( E' \) are identical 
(since isogenous curves share \( L \)-functions).

